==Behind the scenes==
[[File:EYE from FFI Famicom sprite.png|thumb|Sprite from the Famicom release.]]
In the original Japanese version, the EYE and its palette swap the [[PHANTOM (Final Fantasy)|PHANTOM]] greatly resembled a [[wikipedia:Beholder (Dungeons & Dragons)|Beholder]] from ''Dungeons & Dragons'', and was even called Beholder {{J|ビホルダー|Bihorudā}}. Outside of Japan, and for all ports after the MSX version, the design and name were drastically changed, likely due to copyright concerns. The original Beholder design would not be used again until ''[[Dissidia Final Fantasy (2008)|Dissidia Final Fantasy]]'', where it was used for a [[Dissidia Final Fantasy (2008) player icons|player icon]].

